newsitem.title: FRANCE: Four ships loading wheat in Rouen, seven more due.
newsitem.headline: Four ships loading wheat in Rouen, seven more due.

text.p: Four ships are loading a total of 75,000 tonnes of wheat at Rouen, port officials said on Tuesday.
The wheat is for export to west Africa, Algeria, Greece, and Italy, they said.
Two ships are also loading 85,000 tonnes of barley at Rouen destined for Saudi Arabia and Tunisia.
Seven more ships are expected in port by March 17 to load around 91,000 tonnes of wheat. --Paris newsroom +331 4221 5432
